A 19-year-old man, Sofia Jimoh, was yesterday arraigned before an Ogudu Magistrates’ Court for allegedly being in possession of a weapon and belonging to a secret society. Jimoh, a meat seller, of Akanimodo Street, Mile 12, is facing a three-count charge of conspiracy, belonging to a secret society and possession of a weapon with intent to commit felony. Prosecutor Lucky Ihiehie alleged that the defendant committed the offence on December 4 at about 2 pm at Mile 12. He said the defendant had in his possession, a knife and a shirt with the ‘Eiye confraternity’ logo and colour on it. Jimoh pleaded not guilty. Magistrate E. Kubeinje granted him N50,000 bail, with one surety in the like sum. She said the surety must be employed and must provide evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government. Kubeinje adjourned till February 6. 